The first step in the process of product design is to identify the problem that the product is meant to solve. This can be done through market research, or by talking to potential customers. Once the problem has been identified, the next step is to come up with a solution.
The solution can be anything from a new product to a new way of doing something. Once the solution has been decided on, the next step is to create a prototype. This is a physical or digital representation of the product that can be used to test the solution.
The prototype is then tested to see if it solves the problem. If it does not, the process starts over again. If it does, the next step is to create a final product. This is the product that will be sold to customers.
The final product is then tested to make sure that it meets all of the requirements. If it does not, the process starts over again. If it does, the product is then released to the market.
